---
Source:
  - Title: Treasury of Traditional Wisdom
    Page: 158
By: Sextus the Pythagorean
Tags:
  - Sacrifice-Death=Renunciation-Detachment=Spiritual Poverty
  - 160
---
God. indeed, is not in want of any thing, but the wise man is in want of God
alone. He, therefore, who is in want but of few things, and those necessary,
emulates him who is in want of nothing.
